Sentencas: BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-delta (BSCF) materials with perovskite structure were synthesized via solid-state reaction.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Their structural characteristics, electrical-conduction behavior and cathode performance were investigated.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared to A-site elements, B-site elements show a wide solid-solution range in BSCF.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical-conduction behavior of BSCF obeys the small polaron-hopping mechanism.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An increase of Ba or Co content in the BSCF samples results in a decrease of electrical conductivity, which is mainly attributable to the preferential existence of B3+ rather than B4+ in Ba- or Co-rich samples.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At the same time, this leads to increases in the lattice parameter a and the number of oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: BSCF samples with high Ba content show a high structural stability (high oxygen-loss temperature).
Titulo: Preparation and properties of BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ba0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta and Ba0.5Sr0.5CO0.8Fe0.2O3-delta materials present good thermal-cycling stability of the electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta, Ba(0.6)Sr0(.4)CO(0.8)Fe(0.2)O(3-delta) exhibits a better cathode performance in a Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta (GDC)-supported halfcell.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell performance can be improved by introducing a certain amount of GDC electrolyte into the BSCF cathode material.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of BaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
